      "date": "2026-02-09 08:06:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI attempted to fix the build errors present in this patch and succeeded. Yay! Now, keep in mind I barely have any idea what I am doing, so please doublecheck the changes I made to make sure they make sense.\n\nThis service is only provided in hopes to be useful and reduce latency from push to getting actual results in the face of trivial code errors\n\nHere's summary of my changes:\nExcellent! The fix is complete and correct.\n\n## Summary\n\n**The Fix:**\nRemoved the erroneous duplicate function signature at lines 5460-5462 that was accidentally inserted between `EXPORT_SYMBOL(lnet_set_reply_msg_len);` and the kernel-doc comment for `LNetGet()`.\n\n**Rationale:**\nThe patch inadvertently introduced a malformed function declaration:\n```c\nLNetGet(struct lnet_nid *self, struct lnet_handle_md mdh,\n\tstruct lnet_processid *target, unsigned int portal,\n\t__u64 match_bits, unsigned int offset, bool recovery)\n```\n\nThis declaration had several critical problems:\n1. **Missing return type** - causing the compiler error \"return type defaults to 'int'\"\n2. **No function body** - just a signature followed by a kernel-doc comment and then the actual function definition\n3. **Created a syntax error** - the compiler expected either a semicolon (for a forward declaration) or an opening brace (for a function definition), but instead found a kernel-doc comment\n\nThe actual, correct function definition with return type `int` and function body was already present starting at line 5490 (after the fix). The duplicate signature was simply a copy-paste error during the patch creation that needed to be removed.\n\n\nRequest ID: 3654ffde-5283-428f-a1de-21188e0960b0",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
